<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Hardware - Tag - Sidnei Weber</title><link>https://sidneiweber.com.br/tags/hardware/</link><description>Sidnei Weber</description><generator>Hugo 0.139.2 &amp; FixIt v0.3.15</generator><language>pt-br</language><copyright>This work is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0 International License.</copyright><lastBuildDate>Tue, 23 Apr 2013 12:00:50 -0300</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://sidneiweber.com.br/tags/hardware/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Mudando o nome da placa de rede</title><link>https://sidneiweber.com.br/mudando-o-nome-da-placa-de-rede/</link><pubDate>Tue, 23 Apr 2013 12:00:50 -0300</pubDate><guid>https://sidneiweber.com.br/mudando-o-nome-da-placa-de-rede/</guid><description>&lt;p>Semana passada me deparei com a seguinte situação, tinha um servidor com  duas placas de rede , eth0 e eth1 , só que a placa de rede eth0 deu pau e foi trocada, porem, quando foi instalada a nova placa o servidor reconheceu como eth2s.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Para resolver essa situação faça o seguinte:&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Com o usuário root edite o arquivo:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">vi /etc/udev/rules.d/70-persistent-net.rules&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>Apague as linhas:&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img loading="lazy" src="http://ediomaico.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/70-persistent-net-rules.jpg" alt="netrules" srcset="http://ediomaico.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/70-persistent-net-rules.jpg?size=small, http://ediomaico.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/70-persistent-net-rules.jpg?size=medium 1.5x, http://ediomaico.files.wordpress.com/2011/03/70-persistent-net-rules.jpg?size=large 2x" data-title="netrules" style="background: url(/images/loading.min.svg) no-repeat center;" onload="this.title=this.dataset.title;for(const i of ['style', 'data-title','onerror','onload']){this.removeAttribute(i);}this.dataset.lazyloaded='';" onerror="this.title=this.dataset.title;for(const i of ['style', 'data-title','onerror','onload']){this.removeAttribute(i);}"/>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Hardware - Guia ilustrado</title><link>https://sidneiweber.com.br/hardware-guia-ilustrado/</link><pubDate>Tue, 29 Sep 2009 01:29:00 -0300</pubDate><guid>https://sidneiweber.com.br/hardware-guia-ilustrado/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;img loading="lazy" src="http://cabelovivaolinux.files.wordpress.com/2009/07/guia-hardware.png" alt="hardware" srcset="http://cabelovivaolinux.files.wordpress.com/2009/07/guia-hardware.png?size=small, http://cabelovivaolinux.files.wordpress.com/2009/07/guia-hardware.png?size=medium 1.5x, http://cabelovivaolinux.files.wordpress.com/2009/07/guia-hardware.png?size=large 2x" data-title="hardware" style="background: url(/images/loading.min.svg) no-repeat center;" onload="this.title=this.dataset.title;for(const i of ['style', 'data-title','onerror','onload']){this.removeAttribute(i);}this.dataset.lazyloaded='';" onerror="this.title=this.dataset.title;for(const i of ['style', 'data-title','onerror','onload']){this.removeAttribute(i);}"/>&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>